          <h3>What is CSS Minification</h3>

          <p>CSS minification is the process of reducing the size of a stylesheet by removing unnecessary characters such as spaces, comments, and line breaks. This helps websites load faster by decreasing file size without affecting how styles are applied. Using a CSS minifier online ensures better performance and improved user experience across devices.</p>

          <h3>What is CSS Unminification</h3>

<p>CSS unminification converts compressed CSS code back into a readable format with proper spacing and structure. This is useful for developers who need to edit or debug styles efficiently. A CSS unminify tool allows you to quickly understand and modify production-level code without confusion.</p>

<h3>How It Works</h3>

<p>Using this CSS minifier and unminifier tool is simple and fast:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Paste your CSS code into the input field</li>
  <li>Click on “Minify” to compress the stylesheet</li>
  <li>Click on “Unminify” to restore readable formatting</li>
  <li>Copy the processed CSS and use it in your project</li>
</ol>

<p>This process works instantly in your browser without any setup.</p>

